Key Match Events: Finn Allen was dismissed twice via lbw, with no reviews successful after the second dismissal.
Devon Conway was run out via a direct hit from Shadab Khan at mid-off.
Pakistan's spinners dominated New Zealand's innings after the powerplay, limiting them to a pedestrian total of 152-4.
Post-Match Reflections: Kane Williamson acknowledged Pakistan's outstanding performance and admitted that New Zealand were not at their best during the match.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was New Zealand's 12th time reaching the final four of a global tournament but their first time in the final without having won a trophy.
